name: phosphate rock beneficiation | phosphate rock, beneficiated | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/22517/documentation

Large uncertainties exist for data on particle emissions from transfer and storage. Also data of emissions to water and soil are uncertain due to missing data of uncontrolled run off and water use which were estimated. Energy consumption data related to mass of rock moved.;The datasets was updated from producing 'phosphate rock, as P2O5, beneficiated, dry' into 'phosphate rock, beneficiated' and therefore the dataset has been scaled with a factor of 0.32 kg of phosphate rock, beneficiated per kg of phosphate rock, as P2O5, beneficiated, dry.



Mining process, transport to beneficiation plant, dry processing including crushing, screening or washing and flotation.Drying orcalcination of washed rock included. Land use for mining and reclamation.
category: B:Mining and quarrying/08:Other mining and quarrying/089:Mining and quarrying n.e.c./0891:Mining of chemical and fertilizer minerals

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Time of literature publication. Measurements took place partly before this period.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Assumption for production in Morocco based mainly on data from Florida. Some data from Moroccan mines. Various processes with location RER used.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: U.S. technology for dry rock or dried wet rock processing. Average technology mix modelled. No specific age of technology modelled
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Extrapolation and transformation from U.S. data with help of specific informations from literature on Moroccan mines. No extrapolation for energy data.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data for emissions and land use based on various studies from Florida. Energy data based on a world-wide survey and some assumptions. Further data from Moroccan studies, literature and estimations.

exchanges.description: Uncertainty not applicable for output
